01:02:20,370 --> 01:02:22,820
and one day when I came
home from my camping trip

1043
01:02:24,210 --> 01:02:26,160
my mom was in the rocking chair crying.

1044
01:02:27,320 --> 01:02:28,720
She told me she was leaving.

1045
01:02:29,880 --> 01:02:31,430
- Do you remember how you felt?

1046
01:02:35,940 --> 01:02:39,040
- I asked her if she could
stay for my birthday.

1047
01:02:39,040 --> 01:02:39,873
She said no.

1048
01:02:43,190 --> 01:02:46,320
- Do you and your dad do
lots of things together?

1049
01:02:46,320 --> 01:02:48,480
- Well, he's pretty busy.

1050
01:02:48,480 --> 01:02:49,830
You know, he travels a lot,

1051
01:02:50,670 --> 01:02:52,320
but he takes me great places

1052
01:02:52,320 --> 01:02:54,590
for trips and on the weekends and stuff.

1053
01:02:54,590 --> 01:02:56,120
- Like where?

1054
01:02:56,120 --> 01:02:57,290
- Fishing in Alaska.

1055
01:02:58,606 --> 01:03:00,030
He took me snorkeling in Hawaii

1056
01:03:00,030 --> 01:03:01,930
and there was all these eels and fish.

1057
01:03:03,110 --> 01:03:05,450
Pretty neat because you
could almost pet the fish,

1058
01:03:05,450 --> 01:03:09,180
but they swam away just
before you could get to them.

1059
01:03:11,190 --> 01:03:13,610
So, how do you decide who gets adopted?

1060
01:03:16,750 --> 01:03:18,550
- Tell me about your friend Claudia.

1061
01:03:21,190 --> 01:03:23,440
- Well, she taught me
about plants and stuff.

1062
01:03:25,770 --> 01:03:27,300
I know when people are
pretending to like me,

1063
01:03:27,300 --> 01:03:30,230
but she really likes being with me.

1064
01:03:30,230 --> 01:03:33,640
We don't do anything
special except drive around,

1065
01:03:33,640 --> 01:03:34,790
go to the grocery shop.

1066
01:03:36,640 --> 01:03:39,030
She never looks at her
watch when she's with me.

1067
01:03:40,350 --> 01:03:44,290
She always asked me what I'm
thinking about and how I feel.

1068
01:03:44,290 --> 01:03:45,620
She really wants to know.

1069
01:03:47,240 --> 01:03:48,240
- You must miss her.

1070
01:03:51,290 --> 01:03:55,090
- Feels bad all the time in here.

1071
01:04:00,130 --> 01:04:02,550
- Some peoples hearts
are all dried up, Joshua.

1072
01:04:03,620 --> 01:04:05,670
You can hear them rattling around inside.

1073
01:04:07,590 --> 01:04:08,690
It won't hurt forever,

1074
01:04:09,910 --> 01:04:11,760
and it's good to know you've got one.

1075
01:04:18,190 --> 01:04:22,040
- You are not going to
allow a 10 year old child

1076
01:04:22,040 --> 01:04:24,950
to decided what is best
for himself now, are you?

1077
01:04:24,950 --> 01:04:28,270
- The departments evaluation
will be based on my interviews

1078
01:04:28,270 --> 01:04:29,820
with all the parties concerned.

1079
01:04:30,980 --> 01:04:34,260
Joshua is a thoughtful, sensitive boy,

1080
01:04:34,260 --> 01:04:37,130
and I'm sure you're to be
congratulated for that.

1081
01:04:37,130 --> 01:04:40,110
I know that it is not easy
to raise a child alone.

1082
01:04:40,110 --> 01:04:42,220
Especially when you have
a busy work schedule

1083
01:04:42,220 --> 01:04:43,440
and you travel a lot.

1084
01:04:43,440 --> 01:04:44,400
- You know, I'm not so sure

1085
01:04:44,400 --> 01:04:47,880
that I'm concerned about
the counties evaluation

1086
01:04:47,880 --> 01:04:49,820
of my parenting skills.

1087
01:04:49,820 --> 01:04:51,630
Now, do you mind telling me
what are your credentials?

1088
01:04:51,630 --> 01:04:53,830
What qualifies you to judge me?

1089
01:04:53,830 --> 01:04:55,850
- I'm a licensed psychiatric social worker

1090
01:04:55,850 --> 01:04:58,270
with 20 years experience
in child placement.

1091
01:05:02,850 --> 01:05:07,850
- I may not be the most uh,
sensitive man in the world,

1092
01:05:10,250 --> 01:05:13,180
but his own mother walked out on him,

1093
01:05:14,660 --> 01:05:18,420
and I love that boy and
I won't give him up.

1094
01:05:31,218 --> 01:05:34,218
(light piano music)

1095
01:05:39,100 --> 01:05:41,230
- Hi Claude, it's me.

1096
01:05:42,690 --> 01:05:45,020
I'm okay, Chuck's fine.

1097
01:05:47,000 --> 01:05:49,800
Mrs. Kent acted like maybe I
can come and live with you.

1098
01:05:50,830 --> 01:05:52,030
Well, she didn't say no.

1099
01:05:53,810 --> 01:05:56,270
And every Christmas we can go to the farm,

1100
01:05:56,270 --> 01:05:57,420
and I can make a video.

1101
01:05:58,920 --> 01:06:02,990
Yeah okay, I got a new idea
for a story we could work on.

1102
01:06:04,930 --> 01:06:06,630
It's about a screwed up family,

1103
01:06:06,630 --> 01:06:09,260
but the cool part about
it, it's a family of sheep.

1104
01:06:12,690 --> 01:06:14,340
- You want another uh, milkshake?

1105
01:06:16,220 --> 01:06:17,053
- No.

1106
01:06:18,470 --> 01:06:19,900
- More fries?

1107
01:06:19,900 --> 01:06:22,910
- You already asked me
that three times, Dad.

1108
01:06:22,910 --> 01:06:25,400
What is it, why are you acting so weird.

1109
01:06:27,252 --> 01:06:28,652
- I wanna ask you something.

1110
01:06:31,690 --> 01:06:33,580
Was it your idea to call up the county

1111
01:06:33,580 --> 01:06:34,830
and ask to be adopted?

1112
01:06:37,300 --> 01:06:38,133
- Yeah.

1113
01:06:41,135 --> 01:06:42,880
- You sure nobody suggested it to you?

1114
01:06:42,880 --> 01:06:44,510
- No, Dad, like who?

1115
01:06:45,590 --> 01:06:49,740
- Like, I don't know.

1116
01:06:49,740 --> 01:06:50,990
Why did you do it, sport?

1117
01:06:55,840 --> 01:06:59,980
- 'Cause I wanna live with Claude.

1118
01:07:01,630 --> 01:07:03,180
- Well, you just can't do that.

1119
01:07:04,040 --> 01:07:04,873
- [Joshua] Why not?

1120
01:07:04,873 --> 01:07:09,690
- Because, hey look, I may
not be some TV show dad,

1121
01:07:11,000 --> 01:07:12,730
but I'm the only one you got,

1122
01:07:14,010 --> 01:07:15,570
and we were doing okay,

1123
01:07:17,150 --> 01:07:20,650
and I know you want a
mom and a regular family,

1124
01:07:21,850 --> 01:07:24,740
and I'm sorry that it
didn't work out with Claude.

1125
01:07:26,010 --> 01:07:28,310
- It didn't work out with any of them.

1126
01:07:28,310 --> 01:07:30,510
You don't want it to work out.

1127
01:07:30,510 --> 01:07:33,120
Even Mom, you didn't like so much.

1128
01:07:33,120 --> 01:07:37,440
I like having someone to
talk to besides Chuck.

1129
01:07:37,440 --> 01:07:39,590
- You can talk to me, sport.

1130
01:07:41,260 --> 01:07:43,069
- You're never around.

1131
01:07:43,069 --> 01:07:45,870
When you are you're not really there.

1132
01:07:45,870 --> 01:07:48,830
- I was there when you were born.

1133
01:07:48,830 --> 01:07:50,320
I've always been there for you,

1134
01:07:50,320 --> 01:07:53,120
and, and when you go to
college, when you get married,

1135
01:07:53,120 --> 01:07:54,620
I will still be there for you.

1136
01:07:57,357 --> 01:07:59,080
- You could have all your Sunday's free.

1137
01:07:59,080 --> 01:08:01,410
- I don't want all my Sunday's free, Josh.

1138
01:08:03,760 --> 01:08:04,593
I mean, it's just now,

1139
01:08:04,593 --> 01:08:05,910
you got these bureaucratic dogs,

1140
01:08:05,910 --> 01:08:06,743
they're on my back,

1141
01:08:06,743 --> 01:08:08,960
and I gotta prove I'm
not some kind of creep.

1142
01:08:10,253 --> 01:08:12,110
- I never told them you were a creep, Dad.

1143
01:08:12,980 --> 01:08:14,830
I just said I wanna live with Claude.

1144
01:08:25,420 --> 01:08:27,990
- I can't believe Tom would neglect Josh.

1145
01:08:29,110 --> 01:08:31,760
I mean, he'd be more likely to spoil him.

1146
01:08:31,760 --> 01:08:32,910
Buy him too much stuff.

1147
01:08:34,640 --> 01:08:35,473
- But you haven't lived

1148
01:08:35,473 --> 01:08:38,340
with either one of them
for over five years.

1149
01:08:38,340 --> 01:08:41,090
- I've been planning to move
down here since last winter.

1150
01:08:43,310 --> 01:08:45,030
I was only 18 when I had Josh.

1151
01:08:47,740 --> 01:08:50,410
I couldn't take care of
myself, let alone him.

1152
01:08:52,150 --> 01:08:55,480
Well, I tried to five years,
but I wasn't a whole person.

1153
01:08:58,400 --> 01:08:59,810
I was just Tom's shadow.

1154
01:09:00,720 --> 01:09:04,140
He was so much older, I was
sure he'd be the better parent.

1155
01:09:06,190 --> 01:09:07,290
He's done a great job,

1156
01:09:08,340 --> 01:09:09,820
even though he's shuffled a lot of women

1157
01:09:09,820 --> 01:09:11,120
in and out of Josh's life.

1158
01:09:15,750 --> 01:09:17,290
I made a lot of mistakes,

1159
01:09:19,200 --> 01:09:21,100
but I want a shot at being his mother.

1160
01:09:26,060 --> 01:09:28,160
Don't you think I deserve a second chance?

1161
01:09:34,115 --> 01:09:35,850
- Did Joshua's relationship with Claudia

1162
01:09:35,850 --> 01:09:38,340
have anything to do with your decision?

1163
01:09:38,340 --> 01:09:41,328
- No, I decided to try and do this

1164
01:09:41,328 --> 01:09:46,328
before I ever knew about her, I swear.

1165
01:09:49,450 --> 01:09:53,300
- I have a really good
job, and I could move.

1166
01:09:53,300 --> 01:09:55,200
I could afford a small
house with a backyard,

1167
01:09:55,200 --> 01:09:56,033
if that's a problem,

1168
01:09:56,033 --> 01:09:57,680
because I know he would
wanna bring the dog in.

1169
01:09:57,680 --> 01:09:59,330
- Please, calm down, Miss Casara.

1170
01:10:00,590 --> 01:10:03,630
- I'm sorry, it's just that um,

1171
01:10:03,630 --> 01:10:08,160
I've been a little nervous lately.

1172
01:10:08,160 --> 01:10:10,200
I just miss Joshua so much.

1173
01:10:12,440 --> 01:10:14,640
Tom won't let me see him at all anymore.

1174
01:10:15,620 --> 01:10:18,130
You know, he actually accused me

1175
01:10:18,130 --> 01:10:19,700
of trying to get back at him

1176
01:10:19,700 --> 01:10:22,890
by making Josh call you
people about being adopted.

1177
01:10:24,170 --> 01:10:27,870
- Why do you think you and
Josh connected so much?

1178
01:10:29,360 --> 01:10:31,244
- Well, I think because I'm the first

1179
01:10:31,244 --> 01:10:33,850
motherly type girlfriend
that Tom ever had.

1180
01:10:34,700 --> 01:10:36,470
He's dated tons of women,

1181
01:10:36,470 --> 01:10:39,020
but not one of them could've
cared less about Josh.

1182
01:10:40,090 --> 01:10:42,730
- You think Josh was unhappy at home?

1183
01:10:42,730 --> 01:10:44,510
- No, not entirely,

1184
01:10:45,460 --> 01:10:47,820
but I do think that he's a lot needier

1185
01:10:47,820 --> 01:10:49,930
than Tom thinks he is.

1186
01:10:49,930 --> 01:10:51,400
I think that he denies the fact

1187
01:10:51,400 --> 01:10:54,360
that Josh might have emotional problems.

1188
01:10:54,360 --> 01:10:57,190
I mean, he just sort
of says thing like um,

1189
01:10:57,190 --> 01:10:58,610
oh, he's a tough little guy,

1190
01:10:58,610 --> 01:11:01,030
or he's resilient, he'll surprise you.

1191
01:11:02,540 --> 01:11:05,330
- Did you ever see Tom
hurt Joshua in any way?

1192
01:11:05,330 --> 01:11:07,820
Hit him or verbally abuse him?

1193
01:11:07,820 --> 01:11:09,820
- No, absolutely not.

1194
01:11:09,820 --> 01:11:11,410
- Did he ever leave him alone in the house

1195
01:11:11,410 --> 01:11:13,270
for long periods of time?

1196
01:11:13,270 --> 01:11:15,770
- No, not even for short periods of time.

1197
01:11:15,770 --> 01:11:17,730
There was always some sort of housekeeper

1198
01:11:17,730 --> 01:11:22,360
or babysitter there.

1199
01:11:22,360 --> 01:11:27,360
Look um, I would love to be with Joshua

1200
01:11:28,770 --> 01:11:30,700
more than anything in the world,

1201
01:11:31,730 --> 01:11:34,280
and I think that I would
be a good mother for him,

1202
01:11:35,850 --> 01:11:38,870
but I can't tell you that Tom
is some kind of a monster.

1203
01:11:39,880 --> 01:11:42,340
I mean, he's not the most
sensitive guy in the world,

1204
01:11:42,340 --> 01:11:45,040
but he's no worse than
most of the men I've known.

1205
01:11:46,400 --> 01:11:51,400
He's busy, distracted,
enormously self-centered,

1206
01:11:53,880 --> 01:11:55,170
but I don't think that he would ever

1207
01:11:55,170 --> 01:11:56,810
hurt Joshua intentionally.

1208
01:11:58,090 --> 01:11:59,930
- Well, I appreciate your honesty.

1209
01:12:01,670 --> 01:12:05,600
Joshua has told me that you've
shown tremendous respect

1210
01:12:05,600 --> 01:12:07,110
for his thoughts and feelings

1211
01:12:07,110 --> 01:12:09,630
in a way that no one else has before.

1212
01:12:09,630 --> 01:12:11,100
He feels very loved by you,

1213
01:12:14,040 --> 01:12:18,090
but these are very confusing
times, Miss Casara.

1214
01:12:19,370 --> 01:12:21,940
Family relationships are
a lot more complicated

1215
01:12:21,940 --> 01:12:23,000
than they used to be,

1216
01:12:23,000 --> 01:12:24,700
especially for a little boy of 10.

1217
01:12:26,420 --> 01:12:27,950
Children need categories.

1218
01:12:28,990 --> 01:12:30,840
That's how they understand the world,

1219
01:12:31,900 --> 01:12:35,200
and Joshua can not fit
you into any category.

1220
01:12:35,200 --> 01:12:38,670
He can't call you mother,
or step-mother, or aunt.

1221
01:12:42,580 --> 01:12:43,413
Miss Casara.

1222
01:12:44,530 --> 01:12:48,310
- Well, Josh doesn't
call Kit mother either.

1223
01:12:48,310 --> 01:12:53,310
- I know, but he used to,
and in time he may again.

1224
01:12:55,110 --> 01:12:57,030
- But Josh and I need each other.

1225
01:13:00,050 --> 01:13:02,850
- I feel for what you're going
through now, I really do,

1226
01:13:03,940 --> 01:13:06,580
and uh, strictly off the record,

1227
01:13:06,580 --> 01:13:08,850
you could seek legal council.

1228
01:13:08,850 --> 01:13:11,250
You might be able to make
a case for visitation,

1229
01:13:12,570 --> 01:13:13,720
but do think about it.

1230
01:13:15,180 --> 01:13:17,349
I know you care a great deal about Joshua,

1231
01:13:17,349 --> 01:13:19,750
and you want what's best for him.

1232
01:13:26,058 --> 01:13:27,920
- Now, I gotta go to camp.

1233
01:13:32,050 --> 01:13:37,050
Don't worry, boy, you
know I always come back.

1234
01:13:40,500 --> 01:13:42,150
Come on, Chuckles, come on buddy.

1235
01:13:49,330 --> 01:13:51,620
- It's only gonna be
three weeks, you know,

1236
01:13:51,620 --> 01:13:52,640
and at the end of it

1237
01:13:52,640 --> 01:13:55,380
you probably won't even wanna come home.

1238
01:13:56,840 --> 01:13:59,090
Come on, come on, Chuckles.

1239
01:14:00,906 --> 01:14:02,950
- [Joshua] Come on, Chuckles.

1240
01:14:02,950 --> 01:14:05,950
(light piano music)

1241
01:15:34,330 --> 01:15:35,163
- [Josh Voiceover] Dear Claude.

1242
01:15:35,163 --> 01:15:37,500
They made me draw this dumb self-portrait

1243
01:15:37,500 --> 01:15:39,346
in arts and crafts.

1244
01:15:39,346 --> 01:15:41,700
I really hate this camp, it's so dorky.

1245
01:15:43,020 --> 01:15:45,080
I bet Dad forgot to water the garden.

1246
01:15:47,117 --> 01:15:49,720
Do they let dogs live in your building?

1247
01:15:49,720 --> 01:15:51,370
I miss Chuck and Rafe.

1248
01:15:51,370 --> 01:15:52,790
Whenever I miss you,

1249
01:15:52,790 --> 01:15:55,290
I just have to look in my
heart and there you are.

1250
01:15:56,690 --> 01:15:57,523
Love, Josh.

1251
01:15:59,971 --> 01:16:02,971
(light piano music)

1252
01:16:27,260 --> 01:16:31,390
- This is a wonderful story,
darling, and very touching.

1253
01:16:33,510 --> 01:16:34,960
I'll keep my fingers crossed.

1254
01:16:35,960 --> 01:16:38,914
I think any publisher
would be lucky to get it.

1255
01:16:38,914 --> 01:16:40,820
- [Claudia] Thanks, Mom.

1256
01:16:40,820 --> 01:16:42,610
- And some man will be lucky to get you.

1257
01:16:42,610 --> 01:16:44,940
- Mm, I don't want one.

1258
01:16:44,940 --> 01:16:48,900
- You will, and maybe next time

1259
01:16:48,900 --> 01:16:51,490
you'll be more careful
about who you choose.

1260
01:16:51,490 --> 01:16:53,330
- I'll never pick another Tom.

1261
01:16:56,710 --> 01:16:59,000
- Should I tell you about
the man I almost married?

1262
01:17:03,660 --> 01:17:06,880
His name was Jack and he was charming.

1263
01:17:08,500 --> 01:17:10,040
Mama and Poppy didn't approve.

1264
01:17:11,120 --> 01:17:14,210
He wasn't Catholic and he wasn't Italian,

1265
01:17:14,210 --> 01:17:18,060
which is probably why
I was wild about him.

1266
01:17:19,220 --> 01:17:23,540
He was a dreamer and he could
play the piano beautifully,

1267
01:17:25,370 --> 01:17:27,770
and then I met your father,

1268
01:17:29,040 --> 01:17:30,880
and from that first day

1269
01:17:31,800 --> 01:17:36,720
he charged ahead with a
plan for our lives together.

1270
01:17:36,720 --> 01:17:38,660
He was hard to resist,

1271
01:17:41,020 --> 01:17:42,520
and I made the right decision.

1272
01:17:44,180 --> 01:17:48,020
Choose the one who will
sit up with you at 3 a.m.

1273
01:17:48,020 --> 01:17:49,370
when your baby has a fever.

1274
01:17:51,190 --> 01:17:53,380
- Where did you get all
your certainty from?

1275
01:17:53,380 --> 01:17:56,640
- I never had to worry about
making a way for myself,

1276
01:17:56,640 --> 01:17:59,590
or having a career or
living in a city alone.

1277
01:18:00,843 --> 01:18:04,384
Do you know I have never
even called a lawyer?

1278
01:18:04,384 --> 01:18:06,650
- Hmm, I talked to mine again

1279
01:18:06,650 --> 01:18:08,750
after I got the letter
from the department.

1280
01:18:10,620 --> 01:18:13,470
He thinks it's a longshot to
try and appeal the decision,

1281
01:18:15,080 --> 01:18:18,800
but I don't know, I really.

1282
01:18:18,800 --> 01:18:21,180
- Want what's best for Joshua.

1283
01:18:21,180 --> 01:18:23,860
- Oh Mom, I wish you'd
gotten to know him better.

1284
01:18:23,860 --> 01:18:25,930
- I could see he was a lovely boy.

1285
01:18:25,930 --> 01:18:27,700
- There's so much of him in my book.

1286
01:18:27,700 --> 01:18:31,480
I mean, you have no idea
how extraordinary he is.

1287
01:18:33,260 --> 01:18:37,730
He showed me the kind of
person that I need to be with.

1288
01:18:37,730 --> 01:18:39,817
I found out what it's
like to be with someone

1289
01:18:39,817 --> 01:18:42,550
who really cares about you,

1290
01:18:42,550 --> 01:18:44,240
who cares about what you're thinking.

1291
01:18:44,240 --> 01:18:46,750
- Claudia, listen to yourself.

1292
01:18:47,910 --> 01:18:49,710
He's a 10 year old boy.

1293
01:18:50,560 --> 01:18:52,620
- I know, I know it sounds crazy.

1294
01:18:54,400 --> 01:18:56,510
I just miss him so much.

1295
01:18:59,380 --> 01:19:04,380
I finally found someone who
really needed me, a need in me,

1296
01:19:05,940 --> 01:19:09,040
and I just don't think
that I can give that up.

1297
01:19:09,040 --> 01:19:13,300
- You have to, you have no other choice.

1298
01:19:14,410 --> 01:19:16,120
Kit deserves a chance.

1299
01:19:16,120 --> 01:19:17,060
She's his mother.

1300
01:19:19,630 --> 01:19:21,810
It'll be all right, darling.

1301
01:19:21,810 --> 01:19:23,650
You'll have children of your own.

1302
01:19:46,469 --> 01:19:49,386
(knocking on door)

1303
01:19:53,505 --> 01:19:55,340
- Hi, Claudia, I'm Kit.

1304
01:19:55,340 --> 01:19:56,940
- Hi.

1305
01:19:56,940 --> 01:19:58,500
- Thanks for coming.

1306
01:19:58,500 --> 01:20:01,170
I really appreciate it.

1307
01:20:01,170 --> 01:20:02,003
Come on in.

1308
01:20:07,880 --> 01:20:10,480
Did you have any trouble finding it?

1309
01:20:10,480 --> 01:20:13,040
I'm not too good with directions.

1310
01:20:13,040 --> 01:20:14,850
- No, I know Venice pretty well.

1311
01:20:14,850 --> 01:20:17,490
I lived nearby when I first moved here.

1312
01:20:17,490 --> 01:20:18,850
- The neighborhood's pretty weird,

1313
01:20:18,850 --> 01:20:21,300
but at least I can afford it.

1314
01:20:22,620 --> 01:20:25,260
I won't be making too much at my new job.

1315
01:20:25,260 --> 01:20:26,710
- What're you gonna be doing?

1316
01:20:29,281 --> 01:20:31,580
- Uh, I'll be working at the um,

1317
01:20:31,580 --> 01:20:33,490
music center in the box office.

1318
01:20:35,490 --> 01:20:36,430
I start next week.

1319
01:20:39,430 --> 01:20:42,580
That's as close to the
ballet as I could get.

1320
01:20:48,500 --> 01:20:50,210
You wanna see Josh's room?

1321
01:20:50,210 --> 01:20:51,340
He hasn't stayed here yet,

1322
01:20:51,340 --> 01:20:54,110
but pretty soon he'll be
coming every other weekend.

1323
01:20:55,770 --> 01:20:58,130
I uh, tried to fix it
up in a way he'd like.

1324
01:20:59,180 --> 01:21:03,470
- I'm sure it's fine,
but maybe we should just.

1325
01:21:04,840 --> 01:21:06,090
- You know what he likes.

1326
01:21:09,310 --> 01:21:11,420
- All right, I'd be happy to see it.

1327
01:21:14,580 --> 01:21:15,820
- I know Josh loves you.

1328
01:21:19,200 --> 01:21:23,530
He hates me, there's just--

1329
01:21:23,530 --> 01:21:28,530
- Please, don't, he doesn't hate you.

1330
01:21:29,450 --> 01:21:31,270
He just doesn't know you very well,

1331
01:21:32,720 --> 01:21:35,030
and he's probably a lot
different than you remember too.

1332
01:21:35,030 --> 01:21:37,540
You know, he's almost a teenager now.

1333
01:21:37,540 --> 01:21:39,940
- I bet the smell of cheese
still makes him sick.

1334
01:21:41,770 --> 01:21:43,250
- He'll come around.

1335
01:21:43,250 --> 01:21:45,050
You just have to give him some time.

1336
01:21:46,329 --> 01:21:47,529
- Will you give us time?

1337
01:21:50,610 --> 01:21:51,560
- What do you mean?

1338
01:21:54,990 --> 01:21:58,230
- I don't stand a chance
with Josh if you're around.

1339
01:22:01,370 --> 01:22:03,920
I've been a failure at
everything I've tried to do.

1340
01:22:05,470 --> 01:22:07,020
I couldn't make it as a dancer.

1341
01:22:08,880 --> 01:22:10,330
I couldn't make it as a wife.

1342
01:22:16,220 --> 01:22:18,820
Let me try and be a good mother.

1343
01:22:27,328 --> 01:22:28,713
(both laughing)

1344
01:22:28,713 --> 01:22:29,812
- You're fabulous.

1345
01:22:29,812 --> 01:22:30,730
- Oh, thank you.

1346
01:22:32,720 --> 01:22:34,360
- Hey dude, hit me.

1347
01:22:38,255 --> 01:22:42,180
You know, you got a birthday coming up.

1348
01:22:42,180 --> 01:22:44,200
Maybe we oughta figure
out what you wanna do.

1349
01:22:46,170 --> 01:22:50,760
- I wanna go out to dinner,
same as always, but with Claude.

1350
01:22:58,295 --> 01:23:00,710
- Maybe you oughta think about
spending the day with Kit.

1351
01:23:00,710 --> 01:23:03,560
- Mrs. Kent said I'm allowed
to see Claude one more time,

1352
01:23:04,407 --> 01:23:06,157
and I want it to be on my birthday.

1353
01:23:22,646 --> 01:23:24,720
- What about the bathing beauty layout?

1354
01:23:24,720 --> 01:23:25,710
- I don't know.

1355
01:23:28,840 --> 01:23:32,110
- Okay, what's the problem?

1356
01:23:35,390 --> 01:23:37,470
Is the new girlfriend going to be there?

1357
01:23:37,470 --> 01:23:38,520
- Oh God, I hope not.

1358
01:23:40,360 --> 01:23:45,360
No, it's just that I have so many things

1359
01:23:45,650 --> 01:23:47,030
that I wanna say to Josh.

1360
01:23:47,890 --> 01:23:49,630
About how much he means to me,

1361
01:23:49,630 --> 01:23:52,910
and how much I learned
about myself from him,

1362
01:23:52,910 --> 01:23:54,370
and it's just so hard.

1363
01:23:56,225 --> 01:23:57,058
I can't believe this is how

1364
01:23:57,058 --> 01:23:58,770
we have to spend our last time together.

1365
01:23:58,770 --> 01:23:59,800
- I just you would've told him

1366
01:23:59,800 --> 01:24:01,130
it was too upsetting for you to come.

1367
01:24:01,130 --> 01:24:02,680
- No, it's too important to him.

1368
01:24:02,680 --> 01:24:03,770
He picked this event.

1369
01:24:03,770 --> 01:24:06,370
- I know, but your torturing
yourself, it's torture.

1370
01:24:10,780 --> 01:24:12,170
As much as you miss Josh,

1371
01:24:12,170 --> 01:24:14,390
it's being in that
instant fake family again,

1372
01:24:14,390 --> 01:24:15,223
that's killing you.

1373
01:24:15,223 --> 01:24:18,100
With the dad and the kid
and the you playing the mom.

1374
01:24:18,100 --> 01:24:21,090
It's like, it's like a slap in the face,

1375
01:24:22,910 --> 01:24:25,250
and honey, you have got to let go.

1376
01:24:28,740 --> 01:24:30,230
- I really thought I had.

1377
01:24:32,730 --> 01:24:37,730
You know, when I went and saw Kit,

1378
01:24:38,410 --> 01:24:40,830
and she was trying to fix
up that little apartment,

1379
01:24:42,960 --> 01:24:46,690
I realized that motherhood
is more than just attachment.

1380
01:25:28,705 --> 01:25:30,620
- What do you say, sport, lobster?

1381
01:25:30,620 --> 01:25:31,453
- Yeah.

1382
01:25:48,910 --> 01:25:49,743
- Hi.

1383
01:25:49,743 --> 01:25:50,576
- Hi.

1384
01:25:50,576 --> 01:25:52,240
- I didn't think you'd come.

1385
01:25:52,240 --> 01:25:54,540
- I wouldn't miss your
birthday for the world.

1386
01:25:59,190 --> 01:26:01,340
I love the card that
you sent me from camp.

1387
01:26:04,940 --> 01:26:06,340
I'm gonna keep that forever.

1388
01:26:15,873 --> 01:26:17,390
- And there's this real dorky kid.

1389
01:26:17,390 --> 01:26:19,760
I mean, he was swimming and
he really couldn't swim.

1390
01:26:19,760 --> 01:26:22,190
I had to hold onto his hair
until the counselor came.

1391
01:26:22,190 --> 01:26:23,570
- Well, good for you.

1392
01:26:25,150 --> 01:26:27,410
- So, how's your book doing, Claude?

1393
01:26:27,410 --> 01:26:30,791
- Well, I sent it to a couple
of publishers in Boston,

1394
01:26:30,791 --> 01:26:33,541
and hopefully they're gonna
let me know something soon.

1395
01:26:34,830 --> 01:26:39,830
Oh, and I changed Andy's name to Joshua.

1396
01:26:43,370 --> 01:26:45,060
- Really, you did?

1397
01:26:46,719 --> 01:26:49,719
(light piano music)

1398
01:26:55,880 --> 01:26:56,810
- All right (laughs).

1399
01:26:58,971 --> 01:26:59,920
Did you make a wish?

1400
01:27:01,050 --> 01:27:01,950
- Yeah Dad, I did.

1401
01:27:05,850 --> 01:27:10,590
- Well, we thought maybe we'd
check it out, just this year.

1402
01:27:11,693 --> 01:27:14,693
(light piano music)

1403
01:27:35,070 --> 01:27:39,300
Josh, maybe you oughta give Kit a break.

1404
01:27:40,580 --> 01:27:42,080
It's only every other weekend.

1405
01:27:45,020 --> 01:27:49,340
So, don't make her work so hard, okay,

1406
01:27:51,030 --> 01:27:55,390
and try to deal with all
that emotional stuff.

1407
01:27:57,896 --> 01:27:59,550
You don't wanna end up like your old man.

1408
01:28:03,890 --> 01:28:04,723
- I'll try, Dad.

1409
01:28:06,890 --> 01:28:07,723
- Okay, sport.

1410
01:28:15,818 --> 01:28:18,342
- Come on Chuck, come on, good boy.

1411
01:28:18,342 --> 01:28:21,092
(Chuckles barks)

1412
01:28:35,780 --> 01:28:37,670
Ooh Chuckles, your favorite.

1413
01:28:37,670 --> 01:28:40,204
Just like the ones on the beach, yeah.

1414
01:28:40,204 --> 01:28:41,920
- All right, look what I've got.

1415
01:28:41,920 --> 01:28:43,060
- Oh great.

1416
01:28:43,060 --> 01:28:44,220
- Yeah, they almost done?

1417
01:28:44,220 --> 01:28:47,040
- Yep, I cooked the
first one for Chuckles.

1418
01:28:47,040 --> 01:28:48,180
- For Chuckles?

1419
01:28:48,180 --> 01:28:49,013
- Yeah.

1420
01:28:49,013 --> 01:28:50,390
- [Kit] All right, well,
I'll get you a bun.

1421
01:28:50,390 --> 01:28:51,223
- [Joshua] Okay.

1422
01:28:53,792 --> 01:28:58,690
- Okay, all right, there you go.

1423
01:28:58,690 --> 01:29:01,410
- Mm Chuckles, your favorite, yeah.

1424
01:29:01,410 --> 01:29:03,030
- He does like it.

1425
01:29:03,030 --> 01:29:03,863
- Yep.

1426
01:29:06,460 --> 01:29:07,820
- Surprise.

1427
01:29:07,820 --> 01:29:08,653
- Ooh.

1428
01:29:11,651 --> 01:29:12,850
- I can't believe it.

1429
01:29:12,850 --> 01:29:13,900
- How about changes?

1430
01:29:13,900 --> 01:29:15,390
- Nope, all they want me to do

1431
01:29:15,390 --> 01:29:17,135
